{"id":"project-LICHEN-69zc","title":"CBOR encoding in build_info_cbor truncates lengths > 255","description":"File: rust/lichen-oscore/src/lib.rs
Lines: 879-886

When encoding the L (output length) field for HKDF info:
```rust
if out_len <= 23 {
    buf[off] = out_len as u8;
    off += 1;
} else {
    buf[off] = 0x18;  // 1-byte uint follows
    buf[off + 1] = out_len as u8;  // TRUNCATES if out_len > 255
    off += 2;
}
```

The 0x18 CBOR prefix indicates a 1-byte unsigned integer follows, but out_len is usize. If out_len > 255, the cast to u8 silently truncates.

Currently not exploitable because callers only pass KEY_LEN (16) or NONCE_LEN (13), but this is a latent bug if the function is reused for larger outputs.

Impact: Would produce incorrect HKDF info, leading to wrong derived keys.

Fix: Add bounds check or use 0x19 (2-byte uint) for larger values.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:37:28.114769Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:37:28.11481Z"}

